name: gyudon
notes: |
  Andy Cooks' gyudon — Japanese stewed beef & onion bowl
  (https://youtu.be/M-PuGg7Ek-w).
  Serve over rice (cook separately in a rice cooker). Poaching the beef gently keeps it tender.
ingredients:
  - item: beef
    mass: 180
    note: lean/economical cut, sliced thin against the grain; ~150-180g per person
  - item: brown onion
    qty: 1
    unit: ea
    note: sliced; lots — it cooks down
  - item: water
    mass: 100
  - item: dashi powder
    qty: 1
    unit: packet
  - mirin
  - sake
  - soy sauce
  - item: garlic
    qty: 1
    unit: clove
    note: finely grated
  - item: ginger
    note: small piece, finely grated
  - item: egg
    qty: 1
    unit: ea
    note: soft-boiled
  - spring onions
  - rice
  - pink pickled ginger
  - sesame seeds
steps:
  - soft-boil an egg for 6 mins, then shock in cold water and peel
  - bring water to a simmer and add dashi powder, mirin, sake and soy sauce
  - grate in garlic and ginger, keep at a very gentle simmer (no salt needed — dashi has it)
  - add sliced onion and cook down until soft
  - add the thin beef and poach gently until just cooked and a little fat renders; add a splash of water if dry
  - taste and adjust salt; heat off, stir through most of the spring onions
  - serve over rice, topped with the soft-boiled egg, pink pickled ginger, remaining spring onion greens and sesame seeds
